<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="23Jan1918"><font color="red">23 January 1918</font>, <cite>Pound Letters</cite> (Ezra Pound to LR): James Joyce sends the following corrections. <br>Ep 1 p4 par 9 read Cranly&apos;s not Crauley&apos;s <br>1.10 8 after I am, m&apos;am, Buck. etc read  &lsquo;Look at that now,&rsquo; she said <br> &lsquo;We&apos;re always tired etc <br>1.13,7 for  &lsquo;We&apos;re always tired.&rsquo; read  &lsquo;I&apos;m always tired&rsquo; <br>All the first lot of Joyce can go in March. I strongly recommend the omissions AND the comments thereon used in my last. I enclose the Joyce for April.</div>
